    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - MANIFOLDS - INTAKE MANIFOLD</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INTAKE MANIFOLD</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="4">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <para>Remove the following:</para>
            <para>Refer to the appropriate manual section for removal of these components.</para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel Filter Assembly</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel Return Lines (Low Pressure)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel Injection Pump w/High Pressure Lines</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Glow Plug Harness and Controller</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>CDR Assembly</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Air Cleaner (See
                        <emph type="bold">NOTE</emph>)
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After air cleaner removal, install Intake Manifold Cover ZTSE-4136.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>WHEN REMOVING FUEL LINES, THE LINES SHOULD HAVE DUST CAPS INSTALLED OVER ENDS AS WELL AS THE
                        FITTINGS WHERE THE LINES WERE REMOVED. THIS PROCEDURE IS TO PROTECT AGAINST ENTRY OF FOREIGN
                        MATTER IN THE FUEL SYSTEM. USE FUEL SYSTEM PROTECTOR CAP SET ZTSE4136.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove eighteen intake manifold mounting bolts and three lifting eyes,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350208">2.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Keep bolts and lifting eyes together for reinstallation in the same locations. One lifting
                            eye will have been removed when the CDR valve assembly was removed to access the intake
                            manifold.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the intake manifold from the engine to expose the valley pan gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the valley pan drain plug and set aside (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350209">2.9</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four valley pan mounting bolts and washers, then remove the valley pan strap,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350210">2.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove valley pan and gasket assembly. Discard old valley pan, but retain the drain
                    plug.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4350208" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14561" filename="../figcg1/CG14561.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.8 Intake Manifold Removal</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350209" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12322" filename="../figcg1/CG12322.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.9 Remove Valley Pan Drain Plug</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350210" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12323" filename="../figcg1/CG12323.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.10 Remove Valley Pan Strap</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The valley pan and gasket assembly was revised to accept a larger amount of R.T.V. sealant
                            by adding rear corner cutouts. Refer to Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350211">2.11</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4350211" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11923" filename="../figcg1/CG11923.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.11 Valley Pan and Gasket Assembly Comparison</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
